SIMPLE: miniature
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miniature
<hw>Min"i*a*ture</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>miniatura</ets>, fr. L. <ets>miniare</ets>. See <er>Miniate</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>,<er>Minium</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Originally, a painting in colors such as those in
mediaeval manuscripts; in modern times, any very small painting,
especially a portrait.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Greatly diminished size or form; reduced
scale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lettering in red; rubric distinction.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A particular feature or trait.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Massinger.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miniature</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Miniature
<hw>Min"i*a*ture</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being on a small scale; much
reduced from the reality; <as>as, a <ex>miniature</ex>
copy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miniature</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Miniature
<hw>Min"i*a*ture</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To represent or depict in a
small compass, or on a small scale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>miniaturisation</ent>⟦br⟧
